{
  "texts": [
    "Besides the aforementioned downsampling, filters are for instance often used to remove unwanted components from the eye tracker signal.",
    "Like any signal, eye tracking signals contain not only the behavior of interest but also unwanted variability.",
    "Sources of this variability, often called \"noise\", include human behavior and measurement noise of the eye tracker (Mack et al., 2017; Niehorster et al., 2020d Niehorster et al.,, 2021)).",
    "For various uses it is desirable to filter out this noise.",
    "For instance, filtering is often used for interactive applications where gaze data is used online (Špakov, 2012; Feit et al., 2017)."
  ]
}